  levelNumber: 22
  levelName: "Cob\xE1"
  location: Quintana Roo, Mexico
  levelDescription: "Where stone roads crossed the jungle, Cob\xE1 rose with pyramids
    and power.\n\nCob\xE1, meaning \u201CWaters Stirred by the Wind\u201D in Maya,
    was once one of the largest cities in the northern Yucat\xE1n. Flourishing between
    600\u2013900 AD, it controlled trade routes and rivaled Chich\xE9n Itz\xE1 in
    power.\r\n\r\nThe site is famous for its vast network of sacbeob (white stone
    roads), the longest stretching over 100 km, connecting Cob\xE1 to other Maya
    centers. Its most iconic structure is Nohoch Mul, a pyramid rising about 42 meters,
    the tallest in the Yucat\xE1n Peninsula.\r\n\r\nCob\xE1\u2019s stelae record
    dynastic rulers and alliances, offering insight into its political influence.
    Surrounded by lakes and jungle, the city thrived as a hub of commerce, ritual,
    and astronomy. Today, Cob\xE1 remains partly covered by forest, giving visitors
    a sense of discovery as they walk ancient causeways."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: d3a7189a20445cd4a8f2106316a9572d, type: 3}
